<pb facs="Scan20038"/>

<p>United States Consulate<lb/>
Banana "Congo"<lb/>
August 11th 1883</p>

<p>To<lb/>
Hon: John Davis<lb/>
Asst. Secty. of State<lb/>
Washington D.C.</p>

<p>Sir</p>

<p>I have the honor most respectfully
to lay before you the fallowing fact
compelling me to resign my post
Viz. 1st By continuous sickness, I feel
unfit to perform conscientiously my
duty of consul for the United States 
of America</p>

<p>2d Although I have followed my
Doctor's advice and gone South
and North in my jurisdiction; 
I feel my health declining every
day so much so, that I cannot
at time walk with and the help
of a servant</p>

<p>3d My <sic>expences</sic> here for Doctors,
Medicine, and help; are greater 
then I can pay; I parted with</p>

</div1>

